<p>Why is the output different in the below case even when, the variable has been overridden?</p>  <pre><code>public class A {     int a = 500;      void get() {         System.out.println("a is " + this.a);     } }  public class B extends A {     int a = 144; }  public class mainmethod {     public static void main(String args[]) {         B ob = new B();         System.out.println("a is " + ob.a);         ob.get();     } } </code></pre>